 until they become the dominant\ncomponent, and flip the angular momentum of the galaxy in the opposite\ndirection. The final disk-to-total ratio of a galaxy needs to be understood in\nrelation to its stellar mass and accretion history. We quantify the\nsignificance of the stars with different origins and provide them as guiding\nvalues.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 6 May 2019 18:00:06 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 13 Aug 2019 05:31:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-09-25"}
