er, for SN 2016coi we infer\nsubstantial pre-explosion progenitor mass-loss with rate $\\dot M \\sim\n(1-2)\\times 10^{-4}\\,\\rm{M_{\\odot}yr^{-1}}$ and a sub-relativistic shock\nvelocity $v_{sh}\\sim0.15c$, in stark contrast with relativistic SNe and similar\nto normal SNe. Finally, we find no evidence for a SN-associated shock breakout\n$\\gamma$-ray pulse with energy $E_{\\gamma}>2\\times 10^{46}\\,\\rm{erg}$. While we\ncannot exclude the presence of a companion in a binary system, taken together,\nour findings are consistent with a massive single star progenitor that\nexperienced large mass loss in the years leading up to core-collapse, but was\nunable to achieve complete stripping of its outer layers before explosion.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 6 May 2019 18:14:28 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Fri, 19 Jul 2019 17:30:53 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-09"}
